OL,4,CVisa U-turn for stroke survivor's wife
OL,5, The wife of a stroke survivor who was
OL,6, told she must leave the UK to apply for
OL,7, a visa has now had it approved.
OL,9,FLeah Waterman, who is from the
OL,10,FPhilippines, had faced being split from
OL,11,Fher husband Simon who can barely speak
OL,12,Fand needs 24-hour help.
OL,14,FMr Waterman had been told he would have
OL,15,Fto become the sole carer of their two
OL,16,Fchildren at their home in Abergavenny,
OL,17,FMonmouthshire.
OL,19,FBut the Home Office has now confirmed
OL,20,Fthey can stay together.
